# YouTube Live Stream Plugin

The YouTube Live Stream Plugin allows you to embed live streams from YouTube onto your WordPress website.

## Features

- Embed YouTube live streams with a simple shortcode.
- Customize the appearance and behavior of the embedded live streams.
- Settings page to configure YouTube API Key and Channel ID.
- Widget support for easy integration into your website's sidebar or other widgetized areas.

## Installation

1. Download the plugin ZIP file from the [latest release](https://github.com/rizennews/youtube-live-stream-plugin/releases).
2. Upload the plugin ZIP file to your WordPress website.
3. Activate the plugin through the WordPress admin dashboard.

## Usage

### Shortcode

Use the following shortcode to embed a YouTube live stream on any page or post:
[youtube_live_stream]


### Widget

You can also add the "YouTube Live Stream Widget" to your website's sidebar or other widgetized areas. Navigate to Appearance > Widgets and drag the "YouTube Live Stream Widget" to the desired widget area. 

### Settings

Navigate to Settings > YouTube Live Stream Settings to configure your YouTube API Key and Channel ID.

## Compatibility

This plugin is compatible with a wide range of WordPress themes and plugins. If you encounter any compatibility issues, please reach out to the plugin support team for assistance.

